00:03:38,873 --> 00:03:43,119
‘I seek refuge with Allah
from saitan the accursed.

11
00:03:43,599 --> 00:03:47,649
In the Name of Allah, Most
Gracious, Most Merciful.

12
00:03:48,726 --> 00:03:51,920
Allah, there is no God but He,

13
00:03:52,206 --> 00:03:55,968
the Living, the Self Subsisting, Eternal -

14
00:03:56,366 --> 00:03:59,509
 - No slumber can seize Him nor sleep.

15
00:03:59,747 --> 00:04:03,255
His are all the things in
the heavens and on earth.

16
00:04:03,548 --> 00:04:08,722
Who is there can intercede in His
presence except as He permits.

17
00:04:09,155 --> 00:04:13,345
He knows what appears to His creatures,

18
00:04:14,036 --> 00:04:17,655
as before or after, or behind Him.

19
00:04:17,897 --> 00:04:22,722
Nor shall they compass aught of His
knowledge, except as He wills.

20
00:04:23,340 --> 00:04:27,594
His throne does extend over
the heavens and the earth,

21
00:04:27,691 --> 00:04:32,517
and He feels no fatigue in the
guarding and preserving them,

22
00:04:32,568 --> 00:04:36,679
for He is the most High,
the Supreme in glory’.

23
00:04:37,250 --> 00:04:41,615
In the Name of Allah, Most
Gracious, Most Merciful.

24
00:04:43,176 --> 00:04:45,620
‘Say: O people of the Book

25
00:04:45,790 --> 00:04:49,235
come to common terms
as between us and you.

26
00:04:49,502 --> 00:04:51,835
 That we worship none but Allah,

27
00:04:51,994 --> 00:04:54,724
that we associate no partners with Him.

28
00:04:54,841 --> 00:04:57,572
That we erect not from amongst ourselves,

29
00:04:57,619 --> 00:05:00,269
Lords and patrons other than Allah.

30
00:05:00,556 --> 00:05:03,286
If then they turn back,

31
00:05:03,311 --> 00:05:07,442
say: Bear witness that
we at least are Muslims

32
00:05:07,537 --> 00:05:09,902
bowing to the will of Allah.

33
00:05:10,104 --> 00:05:12,866
Verily Allah has spoken the truth’.

